<item>
            <title>[LU-9850] the patchless client should not allow the patched kernel to satisfy it&apos;s dependencies</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9850</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Due to how dependencies work in RPM (and a bug in how kmod RPMs generate&#160;their dependency lists), on a node where the server and client repos are both configured, YUM&#160;could allow the patched kernel to satisfy the patchless-client RPM&apos;s requirements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add &lt;em&gt;Conflicts:&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;Provides:&lt;/em&gt; to the kernel RPM and &lt;em&gt;lustre-client&lt;/em&gt; RPM to prevent this from happening.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This change also allows one to force the installation of the patched kernel RPM (&lt;tt&gt;yum install kernel-lustre&lt;/tt&gt;) if one desires.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
